Class BuildReplyHandler

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.i2p.router.tunnel.pool.BuildReplyHandler

  • class BuildReplyHandler

    Decrypt the layers of a tunnel build reply message, determining whether the individual hops agreed to participate in the tunnel, or if not, why not.

    • Method Detail

      • decrypt

        public int[] decrypt(TunnelBuildReplyMessage reply,
                     TunnelCreatorConfig cfg,
                     List<Integer> recordOrder)
        Decrypt the tunnel build reply records. This overwrites the contents of the reply. Thread safe (no state). Note that this layer-decrypts the build records in-place. Do not call this more than once for a given message.
        Returns:
        status for the records (in record order), or null if the replies were not valid. Fake records always have 0 as their value
